  "text": "property that the Groth-Sahai statement in our above construction is intended to prove, hence eliminating the need for any NIZK proof at all. We show that the tag-based ATDF constructed in [CITATION_1] from the instance-independent RSA assumption (II-RSA) has this property. Although the assumption is quite strong, the resulting PKENO scheme is extremely practical: it requires only one 512-bit exponentiation to encrypt, whereas the previous DLIN-based scheme of [CITATION_2] requires several (though it is based on a more standard assumption). We note that the resulting scheme (assuming we use the more-efficient version of the BCHK [CITATION_3] transform) is also fully randomness recovering, showing that it is in fact possible to achieve fully (rather than partial) randomness recovering PKENO-compatible ECCA encryption.",
